    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-17T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-17T02:00:00-05:00" n="1031"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1031">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/423: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-17T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 17, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 17—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>831. Embassy’s 828, December 16, 4 p.m.<note n="21" xml:id="d1031fn21">Not
                        printed.</note> According to a Japanese press report the customs at Tientsin
                    was taken over yesterday afternoon by the new regime and the five barred flag
                    raised over the customshouse. However, senior member of the Tientsin customs
                    staff is reported as stating that so far as he was aware no change has taken
                    place in regard to jurisdiction over the customs. The Japanese report may be
                    based on Wang Keh Min’s statement contained in the above-mentioned telegram.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Ambassador and Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
